  <details>
    <summary>Does the star projector need 2.4GHz or 5GHz Wi-Fi?</summary>
    <p>2.4GHz only. This is the most common setup issue. If your router broadcasts both bands under the same name, you may need to temporarily connect your phone to the 2.4GHz band during setup.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>How large a room can the star projector cover?</summary>
    <p>The projector covers ceilings up to about 12 x 12 feet at a throw distance of 5–8 feet. For best results, place it on a nightstand or shelf pointing straight up.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>Can I use the star projector without the app?</summary>
    <p>Yes. The projector has a physical button that cycles through preset color modes and rotation speeds without needing the app or Wi-Fi. The app unlocks full control — 16M colors, timer, music sync — but basic use works offline.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>Is the rotation motor loud?</summary>
    <p>There is a very faint hum from the rotation motor — audible in a completely silent room if you're listening for it, but inaudible once any audio is playing. It's not loud enough to disturb sleep.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>Is the galaxy projector safe for kids' rooms?</summary>
    <p>Yes — it uses LED light, not laser, so it's safe for children's rooms. The rotating stars create a calming, low-stimulation light show that many parents use as a sleep aid. Keep it out of reach to avoid small parts contact.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>Can I use this projector without Wi-Fi?</summary>
    <p>Yes. The projector has a physical button that cycles through preset color modes and rotation speeds without needing Wi-Fi. However, the app unlocks full control with 16 million colors, music synchronization, and timer functions.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>How does the music sync feature work?</summary>
    <p>The app's music sync mode analyzes audio playing on your phone and adjusts the projector's colors and brightness in real-time to match the music's rhythm and frequency. It works with any audio app or music service.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>What is the brightness level and can it be adjusted?</summary>
    <p>The projector is bright enough for most rooms but not for task lighting. Brightness is fully adjustable via the app from very dim to full brightness. This makes it suitable for bedrooms, dorms, and accent lighting.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>Does it get hot or use a lot of electricity?</summary>
    <p>The projector runs cool with no heating issues. Power consumption is minimal — roughly equivalent to a standard LED bulb. Safe to run for extended periods without thermal concerns.</p>
